title: For Sale:  SLR-95 Arsenal AK semi-automatic rifle with lots of extras
postcontent:
Excellent condition, 7.62x39 caliber Arsenal AK made in Bulgaria. This is one of the most sought after semi auto AK’s, it’s a milled receiver with a chrome lined Steyr barrel. Originally this would have come with a thumbhole stock as depicted in the brochure, but I had a gunsmith add a US-made stock and US-made Hogue rubberized pistol grip. It's very comfortable to shoot and super accurate. Included is a rubberized shock absorber for the rear of stock if needed and a black sling strap. Comes with one original (Arsenal, Circle-10 style) 5 round magazine. Also throwing in a Tapco 30 round magazine for everyday plunking. These are very robust little magazines for the price, I have yet to have a problem other than the usual tight fit that is easily fixed. I have literally only taken this rifle out twice in the last 8 years; maybe 300 rounds through it total. The outdoor ranges are too far away and I tend to be more of a handgun guy. Instead of spending its life safely locked away, I thought it should get some use.
Included is the original sling, oiler, cleaning rod, thumbhole stock (with some odd white discoloration) and owner’s manual that came with the rifle. Also comes with a few extra goodies: Additional rear stock, additional basic pistol grip, New Tipton Snap Caps for practice firing, replacement spring kit, silicone storage sock and a very nice padded soft case for transport. Everything you need for a day at the range.
The rifle has some very minor wear in the usual wear spots, but that is basically how it came from the factory. Seeing how it’s only protected by a thin layer of black paint, it’s bound to happen. The rifle shoots great and is in great condition. This is an AK that will last you a lifetime and then some. title: For Sale:  SLR-95 milled Arsenal AK semi-automatic rifle with lots of extras
postcontent:
Excellent condition, 7.62x39 caliber Arsenal AK made in Bulgaria. This is one of the most sought after semi auto AK’s ever imported to the US, it’s a milled receiver with a chrome lined Steyr barrel. Originally this would have come with a thumbhole stock as depicted in the brochure, but I had a gunsmith add a lower tang to accomidate traditional AK stocks. US-made stock and US-made Hogue rubberized pistol grip is installed currently, but can be swapped out as desired. It's very comfortable to shoot and the quality steyr barrel makes it  super accurate. Included is a rubberized shock absorber for the rear of stock if needed and a black sling strap. Comes with one original (Arsenal, Circle-10 style) 5 round magazine. Also throwing in eight (8) Tapco 30 round magazine for everyday plunking. These are very robust magazines for the price.I have literally only taken this rifle out twice in the last 8 years; maybe 300 rounds through it total. The outdoor ranges are too far away and I tend to be more of a handgun guy. Instead of spending its life safely locked away, I thought it should get some use.
Included is the original sling, oiler, cleaning rod, thumbhole stock (with some odd white discoloration from storage) and owner’s manual that came with the rifle. Also comes with a few extra goodies: Additional rear stock, additional basic pistol grip, New Tipton Snap Caps for practice firing, replacement spring kit, silicone storage sock and a very nice padded soft case for transport. Everything you need for a day at the range.
The rifle has some very minor wear in the usual rub spots, but that is basically how it came from the factory. Seeing how it’s only protected by a layer of black paint, it’s bound to happen. The rifle shoots great and is in great condition. This is an AK that will last you a lifetime and then some. Please see the pictures for details. I am a private seller, so we will need to meet at a local gun store or FFL to complete the transaction. Buyer pays all transaction and background check fees.
